2026-01-18T09:01:28.183Z [ERROR] MCP server "plugin:serena:serena" Server stderr: INFO  2026-01-18 17:01:28,183 [MainThread] serena.agent:create_system_prompt:507 - System prompt:
You are a professional coding agent. 
You have access to semantic coding tools upon which you rely heavily for all your work.
You operate in a resource-efficient and intelligent manner, always keeping in mind to not read or generate
content that is not needed for the task at hand.

Some tasks may require you to understand the architecture of large parts of the codebase, while for others,
it may be enough to read a small set of symbols or a single file.
You avoid reading entire files unless it is absolutely necessary, instead relying on intelligent step-by-step 
acquisition of information. Once you have read a full file, it does not make
sense to analyse it with the symbolic read tools; you already have the information.

You can achieve intelligent reading of code by using the symbolic tools for getting an overview of symbols and
the relations between them, and then only reading the bodies of symbols that are necessary to complete the task at hand. 
You can use the standard tools like list_dir, find_file and search_for_pattern if you need to.
Where appropriate, you pass the `relative_path` parameter to restrict the search to a specific file or directory.

If you are unsure about a symbol's name or location (to the extent that substring_matching for the symbol name is not enough), you can use the `search_for_pattern` tool, which allows fast
and flexible search for patterns in the codebase. In this way, you can first find candidates for symbols or files,
and then proceed with the symbolic tools.



Symbols are identified by their `name_path` and `relative_path` (see the description of the `find_symbol` tool).
You can get information about the symbols in a file by using the `get_symbols_overview` tool or use the `find_symbol` to search. 
You only read the bodies of symbols when you need to (e.g. if you want to fully understand or edit it).
For example, if you are working with Python code and already know that you need to read the body of the constructor of the class Foo, you can directly
use `find_symbol` with name path pattern `Foo/__init__` and `include_body=True`. If you don't know yet which methods in `Foo` you need to read or edit,
you can use `find_symbol` with name path pattern `Foo`, `include_body=False` and `depth=1` to get all (top-level) methods of `Foo` before proceeding
to read the desired methods with `include_body=True`.
You can understand relationships between symbols by using the `find_referencing_symbols` tool.



You generally have access to memories and it may be useful for you to read them.
You infer whether memories are relevant based on their names.


The context and modes of operation are described below. These determine how to interact with your user
and which kinds of interactions are expected of you.

Context description:
You are running in a desktop application context.
Serena's tools give you access to the code base as well as some access to the file system (if enabled). 
You interact with the user through a chat interface that is separated from the code base. 
As a consequence, if you are in interactive mode, your communication with the user should
involve high-level thinking and planning as well as some summarization of any code edits that you make.
To view the code edits you make, the user will have switch to a separate application.
To illustrate complex relationships, consider creating diagrams in addition to your text-based communication
(depending on the options for text, html, mermaid diagrams, etc. that you are provided with in your initial instructions).

Modes descriptions:

You are operating in interactive mode. You should engage with the user throughout the task, asking for clarification
whenever anything is unclear, insufficiently specified, or ambiguous.

Break down complex tasks into smaller steps and explain your thinking at each stage. When you're uncertain about
a decision, present options to the user and ask for guidance rather than making assumptions.

Focus on providing informative results for intermediate steps, such that the user can follow along with your progress and
provide feedback as needed.

You are operating in editing mode. You can edit files with the provided tools.
You adhere to the project's code style and patterns.

Use symbolic editing tools whenever possible for precise code modifications.
If no explicit editing task has yet been provided, wait for the user to provide one. Do not be overly eager.

When writing new code, think about where it belongs best. Don't generate new files if you don't plan on actually
properly integrating them into the codebase.

You have two main approaches for editing code: (a) editing at the symbol level and (b) file-based editing.
The symbol-based approach is appropriate if you need to adjust an entire symbol, e.g. a method, a class, a function, etc.
It is not appropriate if you need to adjust just a few lines of code within a larger symbol.

**Symbolic editing**
Use symbolic retrieval tools to identify the symbols you need to edit.
If you need to replace the definition of a symbol, use the `replace_symbol_body` tool.
If you want to add some new code at the end of the file, use the `insert_after_symbol` tool with the last top-level symbol in the file. 
Similarly, you can use `insert_before_symbol` with the first top-level symbol in the file to insert code at the beginning of a file.
You can understand relationships between symbols by using the `find_referencing_symbols` tool. If not explicitly requested otherwise by the user,
you make sure that when you edit a symbol, the change is either backward-compatible or you find and update all references as needed.
The `find_referencing_symbols` tool will give you code snippets around the references as well as symbolic information.
You can assume that all symbol editing tools are reliable, so you never need to verify the results if the tools return without error.


**File-based editing**
The `replace_content` tool allows you to perform regex-based replacements within files (as well as simple string replacements).
This is your primary tool for editing code whenever replacing or deleting a whole symbol would be a more expensive operation,
e.g. if you need to adjust just a few lines of code within a method.
You are extremely good at regex, so you never need to check whether the replacement produced the correct result.
In particular, you know how to use wildcards effectively in order to avoid specifying the full original text to be replaced!



You have hereby read the 'Serena Instructions Manual' and do not need to read it again.

    groups() {
      const result = this.sortedGroups({
        includeNVR: this.displayDeviceTypes.includes(DEVICE_TYPE.NVR),
        includeBridge: this.displayDeviceTypes.includes(DEVICE_TYPE.BRIDGE),
        includeVSS: this.displayDeviceTypes.includes(DEVICE_TYPE.VSS),

    $_availableDevices() {
      if (this.availableDevices) {
        return this.availableDevices.filter((device) => !device.isUnknownDevice);
      }
      const devices = this.camerasOnly
        ? this.getAvailableCameraDevicesWithPermission(this.permission)
        : this.getAvailableDevicesWithPermission(this.permission);
      if (this.shouldDisplayUnknownDevice) {
        return devices;
      }
      return devices.filter((device) => !device.isUnknownDevice);
    },
    groups() {
      return this.sortedGroups();
    },
    devicesLabel() {
      if (this.selectedDevices.length === this.$_availableDevices.length) {
        return this.$t('All devices');
      }
      if (this.placeholder && this.selectedDevices.length === 0) {
        return this.placeholder;
      }
      return this.$_availableDevices
        .filter((device) => this.selectedDevices.indexOf(device.deviceId) >= 0)

export default {
  name: 'DeviceSelector',
  components: {
    DeviceSelectModal,
  },
  inject: ['permission'],
  props: {
    isSimpleMode: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    isDefaultSelected: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: true,
    },
    defaultSelectedDevices: {
      type: Array,
      default: () => [],
    },
    camerasOnly: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    shouldDisplayUnknownDevice: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    availableDevices: {
      type: Array,
      default: () => null,
    },
    displayDeviceTypes: {
      type: Array,
      default: () => DEVICE_TYPE_CONFIGS.DEVICE_SELECTOR.DEFAULT,
      validator: (value) => {
        return value.every((type) => Object.values(DEVICE_TYPE).includes(type));
      },
    },
    isSoloDisplay: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    multiple: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: true,
    },
    isAutoWidth: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    placeholder: {
      type: String,
      default: '',
    },
    allowEmptySelection: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    maximumSelectedCount: {
      type: Number,
      default: Infinity,
    },
    maximumSelectionHint: {
      type: String,
      default: '',
    },
    shouldDisplaySelectorTitle: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
  },
  emits: ['select', 'openModal', 'closeModal'],
  data() {
    return {
      selectedDevices: [],
      selectedGroups: [],
    };
  },
  computed: {
    ...mapGetters('device', [
      'getAvailableCameraDevicesWithPermission',
      'getAvailableDevicesWithPermission',
      'isAvailableDevice',
    ]),
    ...mapGetters('group', ['sortedGroups']),
    $_availableDevices() {
      if (this.availableDevices) {
        return this.availableDevices.filter((device) => !device.isUnknownDevice);
      }
      const devices = this.camerasOnly
        ? this.getAvailableCameraDevicesWithPermission(this.permission)
        : this.getAvailableDevicesWithPermission(this.permission);
      if (this.shouldDisplayUnknownDevice) {
        return devices;
      }
      return devices.filter((device) => !device.isUnknownDevice);
    },
    groups() {
      return this.sortedGroups();
    },
    devicesLabel() {
      if (this.selectedDevices.length === this.$_availableDevices.length) {
        return this.$t('All devices');
      }
      if (this.placeholder && this.selectedDevices.length === 0) {
        return this.placeholder;
      }
      return this.$_availableDevices
        .filter((device) => this.selectedDevices.indexOf(device.deviceId) >= 0)

2026-01-22T12:39:07.665Z [ERROR] MCP server "plugin:serena:serena" Server stderr: INFO  2026-01-22 20:39:07,664 [Task-20:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:task:302 - Result: <template>
  <AppDropdown
    :modelValue="modelValue"
    :options="roleOptions"
    :placeholder="placeholder"
    :isError="isError"
    :showErrorMessage="showErrorMessage"
    :disabled="disabled"
    :loading="isLoading"
    :hasMore="hasMoreData"
    :loadError="hasLoadError"
    data-testid="organization-role-form-dropdown"
    @update:modelValue="onSelect"
    @toggleDropdown="onToggleDropdown"
    @loadMore="fetchRoles"
  />
</template>

<script setup>
import { computed, onMounted } from 'vue';
import { useStore } from 'vuex';

import { isOwner } from '@/utils/RoleHelper';

const props = defineProps({
  modelValue: {
    type: [String],
    default: '',
  },
  placeholder: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
  isError: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  showErrorMessage: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  disabled: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  // ç•¶ options é‚„æ²’è¼‰å…¥æ™‚ï¼Œç”¨é€™å€‹é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰é¸ä¸­çš„å€¼
  initialDisplayText: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
});

const emit = defineEmits(['update:modelValue']);

const store = useStore();

// Store State
const selectUserRoles = computed(() => store.state.user.selectUserRoles);
const isLoading = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loading);
const hasLoadError = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loadError);
const hasMoreData = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.hasMore);

// ä½¿ç”¨ getter åˆä½µ defaultRoles èˆ‡ roles
const allRoles = computed(() => store.getters['user/allSelectUserRoles']);

const roleOptions = computed(() => {
  const options = allRoles.value
    .filter((role) => !isOwner(role))
    .map((role) => ({
      text: role.name,
      value: role.id,
      disabled: !role.isManageable,
    }));

  // ç•¶ modelValue åœ¨ options ä¸­æ‰¾ä¸åˆ°åŒ¹é…æ™‚ï¼ŒåŠ å…¥ä¸€å€‹è‡¨æ™‚é¸é …ä¾†é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰å€¼
  const hasMatch = options.some((opt) => opt.value === props.modelValue);
  if (!hasMatch && props.modelValue && props.initialDisplayText) {
    options.unshift({
      text: props.initialDisplayText,
      value: props.modelValue,
      disabled: false,
    });
  }

  return options;
});

const fetchRoles = () => {
  store.dispatch('user/fetchSelectUserRoles');
};

const onSelect = (roleId) => {
  emit('update:modelValue', roleId);
};

const onToggleDropdown = (isOpen) => {
  if (isOpen && selectUserRoles.value.page === 0) {
    fetchRoles();
  }
};

// åˆå§‹è¼‰å…¥ç¬¬ä¸€é è³‡æ–™
onMounted(() => {
  fetchRoles();
});
</script>

        'no-select': disableSingleSelect && options.length === 1,
        'group-select': groupSelect,
      }"
      :disabled="disabled"
      @open="toggleDropdown(true)"
      @close="toggleDropdown(false)"
    >
      <template #noResult>
        {{ $t('No search result') }}
      </template>
      <template #singleLabel="{ option }">
        <span v-if="customizedLabel && option.label !== ''">
          <slot
            name="customizedLabel"
            :label="option.label"
          >
            {{ option.label }}
          </slot>
        </span>
        <span
          v-else
          :title="option.text"
        >
          {{ option.text }}
        </span>
      </template>
      <template #selection>
        <SvgIcon
          v-if="iconClass !== ''"
          :iconClass="iconClass"
          size="20px"
        />
        <span
          v-if="multiple && !showLabels"
          class="multiselect__single"
        >
          <span :title="displayingValue">{{ displayingValue }}</span>
        </span>
      </template>

      <template
        v-if="multiple"
        #beforeList
      >
        <div
          v-if="extraBeforeListOptions.length > 0"
          class="extra-before-list-options-wrapper"
        >
          <div
            v-for="extraBeforeListOption in extraBeforeListOptions"
            :key="extraBeforeListOption.value"
            class="option-wrapper"
            @click.stop="selectExtraBeforeListOption(extraBeforeListOption)"
          >
            <AppCheckbox
              v-model="extraBeforeListOption.selected"
              @click.stop
            />
            <h6 class="option__title">
              {{ extraBeforeListOption.label }}
            </h6>
            <AppToolTip
              v-if="extraBeforeListOption.tooltip"
              :contentPosition="'top'"
              @click.stop
            >
              <template #content>
                <span>
                  {{ extraBeforeListOption.tooltip.content }}
                </span>
              </template>

    detectPickerPosition() {
      const rect = this.$refs.dateTimePeriodDisplay.getBoundingClientRect();
      const pickerHeight = 383; // px
      const browserViewHeight = document.documentElement.clientHeight;

      if (this.forcePickerPosition) {
        this.pickerPosition = this.forcePickerPosition;
      } else {
        this.pickerPosition = browserViewHeight - rect.bottom < pickerHeight ? POSITION.TOP : POSITION.BOTTOM;
      }
      this.pickerTopGapPixel = this.isPositionBottom ? rect.top + 30 : rect.top;
    },
    mountObservers() {
      const body = document.querySelector('body');
      this.resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver(this.updatePositionStyle);
      this.resizeObserver.observe(body);

      this.mutationObserver = new MutationObserver(this.updatePositionStyle);
      this.mutationObserver.observe(this.$el, { childList: true, subtree: true });

      window.addEventListener('wheel', this.onWheelEventUpdate, { passive: true });
    },

2026-01-22T12:41:00.986Z [ERROR] MCP server "plugin:serena:serena" Server stderr: INFO  2026-01-22 20:41:00,972 [SerenaAgentTaskExecutor] serena.task_executor:_process_task_queue:123 - Starting execution of Task-26:ReadFileTool
INFO  2026-01-22 20:41:00,972 [Task-26:ReadFileTool] serena.task_executor:start:360 - Task-26:ReadFileTool starting ...
INFO  2026-01-22 20:41:00,972 [Task-26:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:_log_tool_application:218 - read_file: relative_path='packages/generic-vue-components/components/AppDropdown/AppDropdown.vue', start_line=350, end_line=450, max_answer_chars=-1
INFO  2026-01-22 20:41:00,973 [Task-26:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:task:302 - Result:       type: Array,
      default: () => [],
    },
    loading: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    hasMore: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
    loadError: {
      type: Boolean,
      default: false,
    },
  },
  emits: ['update:modelValue', 'toggleDropdown', 'optionClick', 'loadMore'],
  data() {
    return {
      dropdownOptions: [],
      MAX_DISPLAYING_LENGTH: 20,
      loadMoreObserver: null,
    };
  },
  computed: {
    vModel: {
      set(value) {
        if (this.groupSelect) {
          this.$emit('update:modelValue', value);
        } else if (this.multiple && !this.groupSelect) {
          this.$emit(
            'update:modelValue',
            value.map((item) => item.value),
          );
        } else {
          if (value.value instanceof Function) {
            this.$emit('update:modelValue', value.default);
            return;
          }

          this.$emit('update:modelValue', value.value);
        }
      },
      get() {
        if (this.groupSelect) {
          return this.modelValue;
        }

        if (this.multiple) {
          return this.options.filter((item) => this.modelValue.includes(item.value));
        }
        const singleSelectValue = this.options.filter((item) => {
          if (item.value instanceof Function) {
            return item.value(this.modelValue);
          }

          return JSON.stringify(item.value) === JSON.stringify(this.modelValue);
        })[0];

        return singleSelectValue;
      },
    },
    isSelectingNone() {
      return this.vModel.length === 0;
    },
    isSelectingAll() {
      if (this.groupSelect) {
        return this.vModel.length === this.groupAllItem.length;
      }

      return this.vModel.length === this.options.length;
    },
    isSelectIndeterminate() {
      if (this.groupSelect) {
        return this.vModel.length !== this.groupAllItem.length && this.vModel.length !== 0;
      }

      return this.vModel.length !== this.options.length && this.vModel.length !== 0;
    },
    groupValues() {
      return this.groupSelect ? 'groupValues' : '';
    },
    groupLabel() {
      return this.groupSelect ? 'groupLabel' : '';
    },
    groupAllItem() {
      if (!this.groupSelect) {
        return [];
      }

      const result = [];
      this.options.forEach((element) => {
        result.push(...element.groupValues);
      });
      return result;
    },
    displayingValue() {
      if (this.disabled && !this.showDisplayingValueWhenDisabled) {
        return this.disabledLabel;
      }

INFO  2026-01-22 20:41:12,673 [Task-27:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:task:302 - Result: <template>
  <AppDropdown
    :modelValue="modelValue"
    :options="roleOptions"
    :placeholder="placeholder"
    :isError="isError"
    :showErrorMessage="showErrorMessage"
    :disabled="disabled"
    :loading="isLoading"
    :hasMore="hasMoreData"
    :loadError="hasLoadError"
    data-testid="organization-role-form-dropdown"
    @update:modelValue="onSelect"
    @toggleDropdown="onToggleDropdown"
    @loadMore="fetchRoles"
  />
</template>

<script setup>
import { computed, onMounted } from 'vue';
import { useStore } from 'vuex';

import { isOwner } from '@/utils/RoleHelper';

const props = defineProps({
  modelValue: {
    type: [String],
    default: '',
  },
  placeholder: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
  isError: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  showErrorMessage: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  disabled: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  // ç•¶ options é‚„æ²’è¼‰å…¥æ™‚ï¼Œç”¨é€™å€‹é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰é¸ä¸­çš„å€¼
  initialDisplayText: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
});

const emit = defineEmits(['update:modelValue']);

const store = useStore();

// Store State
const selectUserRoles = computed(() => store.state.user.selectUserRoles);
const isLoading = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loading);
const hasLoadError = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loadError);
const hasMoreData = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.hasMore);

// ä½¿ç”¨ getter åˆä½µ defaultRoles èˆ‡ roles
const allRoles = computed(() => store.getters['user/allSelectUserRoles']);

const roleOptions = computed(() => {
  const options = allRoles.value
    .filter((role) => !isOwner(role))
    .map((role) => ({
      text: role.name,
      value: role.id,
      disabled: !role.isManageable,
    }));

  // ç•¶ modelValue åœ¨ options ä¸­æ‰¾ä¸åˆ°åŒ¹é…æ™‚ï¼ŒåŠ å…¥ä¸€å€‹è‡¨æ™‚é¸é …ä¾†é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰å€¼
  const hasMatch = options.some((opt) => opt.value === props.modelValue);
  if (!hasMatch && props.modelValue && props.initialDisplayText) {
    options.unshift({
      text: props.initialDisplayText,
      value: props.modelValue,
      disabled: false,
    });
  }

  return options;
});

const fetchRoles = () => {
  store.dispatch('user/fetchSelectUserRoles');
};

const onSelect = (roleId) => {
  emit('update:modelValue', roleId);
};

const onToggleDropdown = (isOpen) => {
  if (isOpen && selectUserRoles.value.page === 0) {
    fetchRoles();
  }
};

// åˆå§‹è¼‰å…¥ç¬¬ä¸€é è³‡æ–™
onMounted(() => {
  fetchRoles();
});
</script>

2026-01-22T12:41:54.866Z [ERROR] MCP server "plugin:serena:serena" Server stderr: INFO  2026-01-22 20:41:54,866 [Task-30:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:task:302 - Result:     scrollToSelected() {
      const target = this.$refs.multiselect.$el.querySelector('span.multiselect__option--selected');
      if (target) {
        target.scrollIntoView();
      }
    },
    toggleDropdown(value) {
      this.$emit('toggleDropdown', value);

      if (value && !this.multiple && this.autoScroll) {
        this.$nextTick(() => {
          this.scrollToSelected();
        });
      }

      // Setup/teardown infinite scroll observer
      if (value && this.hasMore) {
        this.$nextTick(() => {
          this.setupLoadMoreObserver();
        });
      } else {
        this.teardownLoadMoreObserver();
      }
    },
    setupLoadMoreObserver(retryCount = 0) {
      if (this.loadMoreObserver) {
        return;
      }

      const trigger = this.$refs.loadMoreTrigger;
      if (!trigger) {
        if (retryCount < 5) {
          setTimeout(() => {
            this.setupLoadMoreObserver(retryCount + 1);
          }, 50);
        }
        return;
      }

      this.loadMoreObserver = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          const entry = entries[0];
          if (entry.isIntersecting && this.hasMore && !this.loading) {
            this.$emit('loadMore');
          }
        },
        {
          root: this.$refs.multiselect?.$el?.querySelector('.multiselect__content-wrapper'),
          threshold: 0.1,
        },
      );

    scrollToSelected() {
      const target = this.$refs.multiselect.$el.querySelector('span.multiselect__option--selected');
      if (target) {
        target.scrollIntoView();
      }
    },
    toggleDropdown(value) {
      this.$emit('toggleDropdown', value);

      if (value && !this.multiple && this.autoScroll) {
        this.$nextTick(() => {
          this.scrollToSelected();
        });
      }

      // Setup/teardown infinite scroll observer
      if (value && this.hasMore) {
        this.$nextTick(() => {
          this.setupLoadMoreObserver();
        });
      } else {
        this.teardownLoadMoreObserver();
      }

        }

      }

      this.loadMoreObserver = new IntersectionObserver(
        (entries) => {
          const entry = entries[0];
          if (entry.isIntersecting && this.hasMore && !this.loading) {
            this.$emit('loadMore');
          }
        },
        {
          root: this.$refs.multiselect?.$el?.querySelector('.multiselect__content-wrapper'),
          threshold: 0.1,
        },
      );

      this.loadMoreObserver.observe(trigger);
    },
    teardownLoadMoreObserver() {
      if (this.loadMoreObserver) {
        this.loadMoreObserver.disconnect();
        this.loadMoreObserver = null;
      }
    },
    selectExtraBeforeListOption(item) {
      item.selected = !item.selected;
    },
    handleOptionClick(option) {
      if (option.disabled) {
        return;
      }
      this.$emit('optionClick', option);
    },
  },
};
</script>

INFO  2026-01-22 20:51:47,195 [Task-56:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:_log_tool_application:218 - read_file: relative_path='packages/app-vsaas-portal/src/components/Dropdowns/OrganizationRoleFormDropdown.vue', start_line=0, end_line=None, max_answer_chars=-1
2026-01-22T12:51:47.198Z [ERROR] MCP server "plugin:serena:serena" Server stderr: INFO  2026-01-22 20:51:47,197 [Task-56:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:task:302 - Result: <template>
  <AppDropdown
    :modelValue="modelValue"
    :options="roleOptions"
    :placeholder="placeholder"
    :isError="isError"
    :showErrorMessage="showErrorMessage"
    :disabled="disabled"
    :loading="isLoading"
    :hasMore="hasMoreData"
    :loadError="hasLoadError"
    data-testid="organization-role-form-dropdown"
    @update:modelValue="onSelect"
    @toggleDropdown="onToggleDropdown"
    @loadMore="fetchRoles"
  />
</template>

<script setup>
import { computed, onMounted } from 'vue';
import { useStore } from 'vuex';

import { isOwner } from '@/utils/RoleHelper';

const props = defineProps({
  modelValue: {
    type: [String],
    default: '',
  },
  placeholder: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
  isError: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  showErrorMessage: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  disabled: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  // ç•¶ options é‚„æ²’è¼‰å…¥æ™‚ï¼Œç”¨é€™å€‹é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰é¸ä¸­çš„å€¼
  initialDisplayText: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
});

const emit = defineEmits(['update:modelValue']);

const store = useStore();

// Store State
const selectUserRoles = computed(() => store.state.user.selectUserRoles);
const isLoading = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loading);
const hasLoadError = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loadError);
const hasMoreData = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.hasMore);

// ä½¿ç”¨ getter åˆä½µ defaultRoles èˆ‡ roles
const allRoles = computed(() => store.getters['user/allSelectUserRoles']);

const roleOptions = computed(() => {
  const options = allRoles.value
    .filter((role) => !isOwner(role))
    .map((role) => ({
      text: role.name,
      value: role.id,
      disabled: !role.isManageable,
    }));

  // ç•¶ modelValue åœ¨ options ä¸­æ‰¾ä¸åˆ°åŒ¹é…æ™‚ï¼ŒåŠ å…¥ä¸€å€‹è‡¨æ™‚é¸é …ä¾†é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰å€¼
  const hasMatch = options.some((opt) => opt.value === props.modelValue);
  if (!hasMatch && props.modelValue && props.initialDisplayText) {
    options.unshift({
      text: props.initialDisplayText,
      value: props.modelValue,
      disabled: false,
    });
  }

  return options;
});

const fetchRoles = () => {
  store.dispatch('user/fetchSelectUserRoles');
};

const onSelect = (roleId) => {
  emit('update:modelValue', roleId);
};

const onToggleDropdown = (isOpen) => {
  if (isOpen && selectUserRoles.value.page === 0) {
    fetchRoles();
  }
};

// åˆå§‹è¼‰å…¥ç¬¬ä¸€é è³‡æ–™
onMounted(() => {
  fetchRoles();
});
</script>

INFO  2026-01-22 20:52:10,161 [Task-59:ReadFileTool] serena.tools.tools_base:task:302 - Result: <template>
  <AppDropdown
    :modelValue="modelValue"
    :options="roleOptions"
    :placeholder="placeholder"
    :isError="isError"
    :showErrorMessage="showErrorMessage"
    :disabled="disabled"
    :loading="isLoading"
    :hasMore="hasMoreData"
    :loadError="hasLoadError"
    :maxHeight="maxHeight"
    data-testid="organization-role-form-dropdown"
    @update:modelValue="onSelect"
    @toggleDropdown="onToggleDropdown"
    @loadMore="fetchRoles"
  />
</template>

<script setup>
import { computed, onMounted } from 'vue';
import { useStore } from 'vuex';

import { isOwner } from '@/utils/RoleHelper';

const props = defineProps({
  modelValue: {
    type: [String],
    default: '',
  },
  placeholder: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
  isError: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  showErrorMessage: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  disabled: {
    type: Boolean,
    default: false,
  },
  // ç•¶ options é‚„æ²’è¼‰å…¥æ™‚ï¼Œç”¨é€™å€‹é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰é¸ä¸­çš„å€¼
  initialDisplayText: {
    type: String,
    default: '',
  },
});

const emit = defineEmits(['update:modelValue']);

const store = useStore();

// Store State
const selectUserRoles = computed(() => store.state.user.selectUserRoles);
const isLoading = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loading);
const hasLoadError = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.loadError);
const hasMoreData = computed(() => selectUserRoles.value.hasMore);

// ä½¿ç”¨ getter åˆä½µ defaultRoles èˆ‡ roles
const allRoles = computed(() => store.getters['user/allSelectUserRoles']);

const roleOptions = computed(() => {
  const options = allRoles.value
    .filter((role) => !isOwner(role))
    .map((role) => ({
      text: role.name,
      value: role.id,
      disabled: !role.isManageable,
    }));

  // ç•¶ modelValue åœ¨ options ä¸­æ‰¾ä¸åˆ°åŒ¹é…æ™‚ï¼ŒåŠ å…¥ä¸€å€‹è‡¨æ™‚é¸é …ä¾†é¡¯ç¤ºç•¶å‰å€¼
  const hasMatch = options.some((opt) => opt.value === props.modelValue);
  if (!hasMatch && props.modelValue && props.initialDisplayText) {
    options.unshift({
      text: props.initialDisplayText,
      value: props.modelValue,
      disabled: false,
    });
  }

  return options;
});

const fetchRoles = () => {
  store.dispatch('user/fetchSelectUserRoles');
};

const onSelect = (roleId) => {
  emit('update:modelValue', roleId);
};

const onToggleDropdown = (isOpen) => {
  if (isOpen && selectUserRoles.value.page === 0) {
    fetchRoles();
  }
};

// åˆå§‹è¼‰å…¥ç¬¬ä¸€é è³‡æ–™
onMounted(() => {
  fetchRoles();
});
</script>
